      "lineNbr": 93,
      "author": {
        "id": 1398165
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-09T09:46:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It is not in a spawned goroutine by the main flow. After 5 seconds, the `verifySearch()` would return with the python responses to the caller - `SearchBuilds()`, which would return those results to users. \n\nThe reason I added a timeout here is to not be block so long in case the `searchBuildsGoPath()` takes 5 seconds longer than python service. Because the users are still waiting for the response. If the \ngo path takes much longer than py path (which is highly unlikely happen), then just give up the later comparison and directly return.",
      "parentUuid": "a1d27d77_4134e08f",
